div.p:
One male from Medje has the lower breast and abdomen very blackish;

						FIG. 24.  A pair of grosbeak-weavers, Amblyospiza albifrons saturata, and their nest.


  the usual color there is distinctly gray.  The wing length of our males from the northern Ituri is 87–90 mm., of those from Faradje and the eastern Ituri 88–96 mm.  In juvenal dress males resemble the females, and they seem to require more than a year to acquire adult plumage.  In their second year they begin to have some rufous feathers about the head and become a little whitish on the forehead.
